<!--
    Demo Case 01 - Draft / General Inquiry / Low priority
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the FIRST of the 10-case demo dataset; together with
    cases 02 through 10 (which cover the remaining statuses across both
    case types) it satisfies the AAP requirement (Section 0.7.4) of
    "at least 10 demo cases across all six statuses and both case
    types," and contributes to the dataset matrix:

        Case 01 - Draft       / General Inquiry / Low       ## THIS FILE
        Case 02 - Open        / General Inquiry / Medium
        Case 03 - In Progress / General Inquiry / Medium
        Case 04 - Pending     / General Inquiry / High
        Case 05 - Resolved    / General Inquiry / Medium
        Case 06 - Closed      / General Inquiry / Low
        Case 07 - Open        / Complaint       / High
        Case 08 - In Progress / Complaint       / Critical
        Case 09 - Resolved    / Complaint       / High
        Case 10 - Closed      / Complaint       / Critical

    The 10-case dataset thus exercises:
      * Every one of the six statuses (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending,
        Resolved, Closed) - this case occupies the SOLE Draft slot.
        It is the canonical Draft case in the dataset; no other demo
        case has status=Draft. This is intentional: Draft is a transient
        starting state for new submissions, and a single representative
        is sufficient for visualization and transition-guard testing.
      * Both case types (General Inquiry and Complaint) - case 01 is on
        the General Inquiry side. There is no Complaint counterpart to
        case 01 because Draft cases are inherently pre-assignment and
        the demonstration value is identical regardless of case type.
      * Multiple priorities (Low, Medium, High, Critical) - this case
        contributes a Low bar to the all_cases_by_priority chart
        (paired with case 06 Closed General Inquiry Low).
      * The Draft -> Open TRANSITION-GUARD scenario - this case is the
        CANONICAL test input for the validate_open_transition subflow's
        "assigned_group must be populated" gate. With assigned_group
        intentionally absent on this Draft case, any attempt to
        advance this case to Open via the form MUST be blocked by the
        subflow until an assigned_group is selected.
      * The Any -> Draft PROHIBITED-TRANSITION scenario - this case is
        the only canonical reference for "still in Draft." Other cases
        cannot legally be set back to Draft; if an operator attempts
        to back-transition any non-Draft case to Draft, the
        x_[scope]_block_draft_backtransition Before-Update business
        rule MUST surface the verbatim error "Cases cannot be returned
        to Draft." (per AAP Section 0.7.4 / Section 0.5.5).
      * The case_count_by_status Agent Workspace donut's Draft slice -
        this case is the only contributor; without case 01 the donut
        would show no Draft slice at all, which would mask whether the
        Draft choice value is even registered.

    Lifecycle position - WHY Draft / General Inquiry / Low is meaningful:
      A General Inquiry case in Draft status has NOT yet entered the
      lifecycle. Per AAP Section 0.5.5's transition matrix:
        - The implicit start state for a new case is Draft: per the
          dictionary entry at ../../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_status.xml,
          Draft is the default value for the status field. When a case
          is created via the internal form OR via the unauthenticated
          Experience Portal submission widget OR via the seed script
          OR via a Table-API POST, the case enters Draft until an
          intake operator promotes it.
        - The Draft -> Open transition is gated by
          validate_open_transition: assigned_group must be populated;
          otherwise the form-level blocking error is surfaced.
        - Any -> Draft is PROHIBITED ("Cases cannot be returned to
          Draft." per AAP Section 0.7.4); any attempt to back-
          transition another case (e.g. case 02 Open) to Draft MUST
          be blocked by the x_[scope]_block_draft_backtransition
          Before-Update business rule.
      This case occupies the Draft side of those gates: assigned_group
      is INTENTIONALLY ABSENT (the defining feature of Draft in this
      dataset; there is no Complaint counterpart for the Draft side
      because Draft has no type-specific behavior), assigned_agent is
      INTENTIONALLY ABSENT (Draft is pre-assignment and pending_reason
      is irrelevant outside of Pending status). The Low priority is the
      canonical "no urgency" priority - the lowest of the four-step
      priority enum (Low, Medium, High, Critical).

    Role / cross-dependency context (per AAP Section 0.5.2):

      This case DEPENDS ON (loaded BEFORE this record):
        - The scoped application records under ../../app/
            (sys_app and sys_scope; this case's <sys_scope>/<sys_package>
             reference fields resolve via the source attribute against
             those records)
        - The case table definition at ../../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml
            (this record's <sys_class_name>x_[scope]_case</sys_class_name>
             requires the table to exist)
        - All dictionary entries for the case table under
            ../../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_*.xml  (every populated
            field below requires its dictionary entry to be present)
        - All choice records under ../../choices/  (the type=General
            Inquiry, status=Draft, and priority=Low choice values must
            all be registered; the Draft choice is defined at
            ../../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml as the FIRST status
            choice in the lifecycle order and is the dictionary's
            default value for the status field)
        - The auto-numbering record at
            ../../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case.xml  (defines the
            CASE0000001 format; this record's <number/> is intentionally
            absent so the platform auto-generates per that format on
            insert)
        - The role records under ../../roles/  (the demo manager's
            read/write access requires the x_[scope]_case_manager role;
            the demo viewer's read access requires the
            x_[scope]_case_viewer role; the demo agent's read access
            for this Draft case requires the x_[scope]_case_agent role
            BUT the "Assigned only" ACL clause does NOT match this
            case since BOTH assigned_agent AND assigned_group are
            empty - therefore the demo agent cannot see this case
            via the case_agent ACL; only case_manager and case_viewer
            see Draft cases by default)
        - The ACL records under ../../acl/  (table-level and field-
            level ACLs gate read/write access; Draft cases are visible
            to case_manager and case_viewer via the unconditional
            read ACLs but are NOT visible to case_agent under the
            "Assigned only" ACL since neither clause matches an empty
            assigned_agent / assigned_group pair)
        - The business rule records under ../../business_rules/
            (set_opened_date Before-Insert auto-sets <opened_date> on
             this case at import time; the
             x_[scope]_block_draft_backtransition Before-Update rule
             does NOT fire on this case because this case IS the
             canonical Draft - the rule fires when OTHER cases are
             attempted to back-transition to Draft)
        - The flow records under ../../flows/
            (../../flows/general_inquiry_state_machine.xml governs this
             case type; the validate_open_transition subflow at
             ../../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml is the
             guard that will block any attempt to transition THIS CASE
             from Draft to Open while assigned_group is empty - this
             case is the canonical test input for that subflow)
        - NO group / user / role-assignment dependencies under
            ../groups/ ../users/ ../role_assignments/ - Draft cases
            have NO assigned_group, NO assigned_agent, and therefore
            require no upstream sys_user / sys_user_group / role-
            assignment records to resolve any reference fields.
            (The role assignments and demo user/group records are
             still upstream dependencies of the SCOPED APPLICATION as
             a whole, but none are referenced by this particular case
