                        across the dataset)
        No other fields contain PII because no other free-text fields
        are populated on this Draft case.

      Rule 2 - No Auto-Number Override (AAP Section 0.7.4):
        The <number/> element is intentionally absent. The auto-number
        sequence ../../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case.xml will
        generate CASE0000001 (since this is the first case in the
        seed dataset, even though the file is named demo_01 the actual
        platform-generated number depends on insert order; the seed
        script orders cases by file name so case 01 receives
        CASE0000001 in the steady-state seed). Presetting <number>
        would conflict with the auto-numbering counter and may cause
        Update Set preview errors per AAP Section 0.7.3 Validation
        Gate 7.

      Rule 3 - Auto-Set Opened Date (AAP Section 0.5.7 / business rule
        semantics):
        The <opened_date/> element is intentionally absent. The
        ../../business_rules/x_[scope]_set_opened_date.xml Before-
        Insert business rule auto-populates opened_date =
        gs.nowDateTime() on insert. Demo case 01 leaves this field
        empty/absent and lets the BR fire. This means demo case 01's
        opened_date will be the date/time when the Update Set is
        committed on the destination PDI - which is intentional (it
        makes case 01 visible in the cases_opened_30d single-score
        widget). The exception cases (06 and 10) preset opened_date
        because they are seeded directly as Closed and need a non-
        trivial gap between opened_date and closed_date for the
        avg_time_to_close widget; this case does NOT preset
        opened_date because it is Draft, not Closed.

      Rule 4 - No Closed Date in Draft (AAP Section 0.5.7):
        The <closed_date/> element is intentionally absent. Per AAP
        Section 0.5.7's data model table, closed_date is "Auto-set on
        Close transition" - i.e. it is populated only when the case
        reaches the Closed status. This case is in Draft status and
        has not been closed; therefore closed_date is not applicable
        and is NOT set. The set_closed_date Before-Update business
        rule (../../business_rules/x_[scope]_set_closed_date.xml) only
        fires on Resolved -> Closed transitions, which this case has
        not undergone.

      Rule 5 - No Assigned Group / Agent / Pending Reason in Draft
        (AAP Section 0.5.5):
        The <assigned_group/>, <assigned_agent/>, and <pending_reason/>
        elements are ALL intentionally absent.
          - <assigned_group/> empty: Draft cases are pre-assignment.
            The Draft -> Open transition guard validate_open_transition
            (../../flows/sub_flows/validate_open_transition.xml)
            requires assigned_group to be populated; this case
            DELIBERATELY violates that requirement to serve as the
            canonical test input for the guard.
          - <assigned_agent/> empty: Draft cases are pre-assignment.
            Even if an operator pre-populates assigned_agent at Draft
            time, the case still cannot advance to Open until
            assigned_group is also populated; the dataset convention
            is to leave both fields empty on Draft.
          - <pending_reason/> empty: pending_reason is only relevant
            on Pending status. Per AAP Section 0.5.7, pending_reason
            is populated by the validate_pending_transition subflow on
            In Progress -> Pending transitions and cleared by the
            x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress Before-Update
            business rule on Pending -> In Progress transitions.
            Neither path applies to a Draft case.

      Rule 6 - Choice Value Precision (AAP Section 0.5.7):
        type     = "General Inquiry" (capital G, capital I, single
                   space; matching the choice list at
                   ../../choices/sys_choice_case_type.xml)
        status   = "Draft" (capital D, lowercase the rest; matching
                   the choice list at
                   ../../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml; this is
                   the dictionary's default value for the status
                   field)
        priority = "Low" (capital L, lowercase the rest; matching
                   the choice list at
                   ../../choices/sys_choice_case_priority.xml as the
                   first / lowest of the four priority steps)
        Common mistakes to avoid: "draft", "DRAFT", "general inquiry",
        "GENERAL_INQUIRY", "general-inquiry", "low", "LOW" - all of
        these would FAIL choice-value validation against the
        registered choice lists.

      Rule 7 - Zero Hardcoded sys_id Cross-References (AAP Section
        0.7.2):
        The case's OWN <sys_id> below is the record's primary key,
        deterministically derived as MD5("Demo case 01: Draft (General
        Inquiry)") = f4b0e89753f41d01ee1bd8dd3c5b41fc. This is the
        OWN primary key - explicitly NOT a reference to any other
        record's sys_id (the agent prompt rules permit a record's own
        sys_id; only references to OTHER records' sys_ids are
        prohibited). All sibling cases follow this same MD5(subject)
