        re-imports on different PDIs.
        Since Draft cases have no <assigned_group> or <assigned_agent>
        populated, no other reference-resolution concerns arise for
        this case specifically (no group lookups, no user lookups).
        The <sys_scope> and <sys_package> reference fields resolve by
        the display_value / source attributes and the element text
        value, NOT by hardcoded sys_id literals - matching the
        established sibling convention.

      Rule 8 - Scope Binding (folder requirements):
        <sys_scope display_value="Case Management">x_[scope]</sys_scope>
        <sys_package display_value="Case Management" source="x_[scope]">
            x_[scope]
        </sys_package>
        <sys_scope>   binds this case row to the scoped application via
        the display_value attribute "Case Management" and the element
        text "x_[scope]" which the PDI Update-Set engine resolves to
        the auto-assigned scope record on import.
        <sys_package> follows the same pattern with the additional
        source attribute "x_[scope]" identifying the parent scoped
        application package. This convention is established by the
        sibling case records (cases 02-10) and matches the resolution
