                             the record element)
        HTML encoding:       the literal `>` in the description's
                             "Draft -> Open" phrase is encoded as
                             `&gt;` to keep the XML well-formed
        Line endings:        Unix-style LF only (no CRLF)
        Encoding:            UTF-8 declared in the XML prolog

    Source-side semantic reference (per AAP Section 0.8.1, READ-ONLY):

      acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/
      java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java is the
      ArkCase JPA entity that informs the case-domain semantics. The
      ArkCase entity has approximately 80+ fields including identity,
      numbering, classification, title, status, descriptive details,
      incident timestamps, audit, disposition, priority, queue/response
      timing, courtroom/responsibility, ECM container linkage, and
      child associations. The ServiceNow target replicates ONLY the
      12 fields plus pending_reason enumerated in AAP Section 0.5.7
      (number, type, status, priority, subject, description,
      opened_date, closed_date, assigned_group, assigned_agent,
      requester_name, requester_email, pending_reason). All other
      ArkCase fields - cm_class_name, cm_object_type, milestones,
      participants, ECM container, originator, legacy system ID,
      restriction flags, courtroom, response/disposition timing - are
      explicitly OUT OF SCOPE and NOT replicated.

      Key ArkCase semantic anchors that informed the design but are
      NOT byte-for-byte ported:
        cm_case_status (the source for our <status>), cm_case_priority
        (the source for our <priority>), cm_case_type (the source for
        our <type>), cm_case_title (the source for our <subject>),
        cm_case_details (the source for our <description>),
        cm_case_received_date (the source for our <opened_date>),
        cm_case_assignee (the source for our <assigned_agent>;
        ArkCase used a single string for the username, ServiceNow
        uses a Reference field to sys_user resolved by user_name
        lookup - though this case leaves it empty since it is Draft).
        ArkCase's CaseFileQueueHandler @PrePersist lifecycle hook
        (which set cm_case_status = "ACTIVE" pre-save) is replaced
        by the ServiceNow Flow Designer flows under ../../flows/.
        ArkCase's @PrePersist default of cm_case_status = "DRAFT" is
        replaced by the dictionary's default value for the status
        field (also "Draft"), so this case correctly inherits Draft
        as its initial status without explicit override (though we
        DO set status="Draft" explicitly here for record clarity and
        to prevent any ambiguity in the seed XML).

      The ArkCase acm_case_file table and its surrounding Spring
      service classes (SaveCaseService, GetCaseService,
      ChangeCaseFileStateService, CaseFileQueueHandler) are NOT
      replicated - the ServiceNow target uses a brand-new
      x_[scope]_case table with auto-generated Glide records and
      platform-native Flow Designer flows for state-machine logic.

