             Draft contributor)
           - the General Inquiry slice of the all_cases_by_type donut
           - the Low bar of the all_cases_by_priority bar chart
           - the count of the cases_opened_30d single-score widget
             (since opened_date is auto-set to "now" on insert by the
             set_opened_date business rule)
         This case does NOT appear in:
           - the avg_time_to_close widget (filters on status=Closed)
           - the demo agent's "My Open Cases" personal list (filter
             requires assigned_agent = current user, but
             assigned_agent is empty)
           - the case_agent's ACL-filtered case list (BOTH "Assigned
             only" clauses fail)

      8. The Draft -> Open transition USING this case as the input
         is the canonical test in Validation Gate 2 (Workflow). When
         an operator (with case_manager role) attempts to set this
         case status to Open via the form WITHOUT first populating
         assigned_group, the validate_open_transition subflow MUST
         surface a form-level blocking error and the transition MUST
         be denied. After assigned_group is populated on the form
         (selecting x_[scope]_demo_team), the same transition attempt
         MUST succeed and yield case status = Open (matching the
         post-transition state of sibling case 02).

      9. The Any -> Draft PROHIBITED-TRANSITION rule USING this case
         as the reference state. This case is the canonical "still in
         Draft" reference. When an operator attempts to back-
         transition any non-Draft case (e.g. case 02 Open) to Draft
         via the form, the x_[scope]_block_draft_backtransition
         Before-Update business rule MUST surface the verbatim error
         "Cases cannot be returned to Draft." (per AAP Section 0.7.4)
         and the update MUST be aborted. This case demonstrates the
         legitimate Draft terminus for net-new cases.

     10. The literal "[scope]" placeholder is preserved verbatim
         throughout the file - in the sys_class_name, sys_update_name,
         table attribute, inner element name, all cross-reference
         text values, and the file path. The PDI substitutes the
         auto-assigned concrete scope id at apply-time;
         pre-substituting here would break the substitution mechanism.
-->
